	1.	Loads all .parquet files in a folder (like uploaded_files/anomaly_detection_results)
	2.	For each file (per device), reads is_anomaly, template_id, orig_timestamp, device_id
	3.	Calculates:
	•	total rows
	•	total anomalies (is_anomaly == 1)
	•	anomaly rate
	•	unique template count
	•	top anomaly templates
	•	earliest and latest orig_timestamp
	4.	Outputs two CSVs:
	•	One combined summary CSV for all devices
	•	One individual CSV per device in a folder extracted_anomaly_features

Optional: Skip rows with invalid or very old timestamps (older than 30 days)